abstract: President Donald Trump's reelection campaign is mustering governmental muscle as it tries to turn out Republican voters next month in early voting Iowa.
snippet: President Donald Trump's reelection campaign is mustering governmental muscle as it tries to turn out Republican voters next month in early voting Iowa.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's reelection campaign is mustering governmental muscle as it tries to turn out Republican voters next month in early voting Iowa.
headline_main: Trump Officials and Backers to Flood Iowa on Caucus Day
headline_print_headline: Trump Officials and Backers to Flood Iowa on Caucus Day

abstract: Britain's Prince Andrew has provided “zero cooperation” to the American investigators who want to interview him as part of their sex trafficking probe into Jeffrey Epstein, a U.S. prosecutor said Monday.
snippet: Britain's Prince Andrew has provided “zero cooperation” to the American investigators who want to interview him as part of their sex trafficking probe into Jeffrey Epstein, a U.S. prosecutor said Monday.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Britain's Prince Andrew has provided “zero cooperation” to the American investigators who want to interview him as part of their sex trafficking probe into Jeffrey Epstein, a U.S. prosecutor said Monday.
headline_main: Prince Andrew Called Uncooperative in Jeffrey Epstein Probe
headline_print_headline: Prince Andrew Called Uncooperative in Jeffrey Epstein Probe

abstract: Mr. Taylor’s rebuke of Mr. Pompeo is also a not-so-subtle reminder to the president and his Republican allies of the national security threat at the heart of the Democratic case
snippet: Mr. Taylor’s rebuke of Mr. Pompeo is also a not-so-subtle reminder to the president and his Republican allies of the national security threat at the heart of the Democratic case
lead_paragraph: One of the key prosecution witnesses at the center of President Trump’s impeachment trial on Sunday lectured Secretary of State Mike Pompeo — and, without directly saying so, Mr. Trump — about the importance of supporting Ukraine. William B. Taylor Jr., the former top American diplomat in Ukraine, took issue with Mr. Pompeo for reportedly questioning whether Americans care about that country. In an op-ed published in The New York Times, Mr. Taylor described the many reasons Ukraine, a country wedged between Russia and the countries of NATO, is vital to the United States.

abstract: The British royal said he would help American officials investigating  possible sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein’s associates, but so far he has ignored their requests.
snippet: The British royal said he would help American officials investigating  possible sex trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein’s associates, but so far he has ignored their requests.
lead_paragraph: Two months ago, Britain’s Prince Andrew issued a public statement saying he would be willing to help American law enforcement officials with their investigation into allegations of sex-trafficking by Jeffrey Epstein and his associates.

headline_main: Trump says he has not seen Bolton’s manuscript.

abstract: Senators Mitch McConnell and Lindsey Graham were among those angrily pressing the White House about Bolton’s account.
snippet: Senators Mitch McConnell and Lindsey Graham were among those angrily pressing the White House about Bolton’s account.
lead_paragraph: Among the Senate Republicans angry at the White House on Monday over revelations about a manuscript submitted for review by John R. Bolton are top allies of President Trump, including Senator Mitch McConnell, the majority leader.

abstract: For the first time in years, Federal Reserve officials will hold their latest policy meeting this week feeling broadly satisfied with where interest rates are and with seemingly no inclination to change them anytime soon.

abstract: The Maine Republican has already signaled she will vote in favor of calling witnesses.
snippet: The Maine Republican has already signaled she will vote in favor of calling witnesses.
lead_paragraph: Senator Susan Collins, Republican of Maine and one of the most closely watched swing votes on calling witnesses, said in a statement on Monday that new revelations from John R. Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, “strengthen the case for witnesses” in President Trump’s impeachment trial.

headline_main: Collins says Bolton revelations ‘strengthen the case for witnesses.’

abstract: One example of ammunition: a news conference from two decades ago by a current Democratic House manager.
snippet: One example of ammunition: a news conference from two decades ago by a current Democratic House manager.
lead_paragraph: In the wake of weekend revelations from John R. Bolton, President Trump’s former national security adviser, Republican defenders of Mr. Trump are looking for any ammunition to undercut the Democratic argument in favor of calling new witnesses.
headline_main: Republicans look for reasons to avoid calling witnesses.
